// pond/agent/conversation — bus topics.
//
// One typed pub/sub channel: `ConversationUpdated` fires once
// per successful `append()` on a Conversation. The payload is
// the Message that was just appended — subscribers reconstruct
// the post-append history by composing the incoming message onto
// their mirror of the prior state.
//
// Per CONTRACTS.md this is a topic-decl (not a literal-string
// bus subject) so subscribers reference it as
// `conv::ConversationUpdated` under the suggested `conv` alias.
//
// **Per-conversation subject derivation gap.** Two distinct
// Conversation instances that both publish on `ConversationUpdated`
// share a single wire subject in v1 — every subscriber sees
// every conversation's traffic. The intended end-state is one
// hierarchical-topic per conversation
// (`topic SessionA : ConversationUpdated { subject: "session_a"; }`)
// so consumers filter at the bus level. See FRICTION.md.

topic ConversationUpdated { payload: Message; }
